{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "6151e86323833ce6aaa28f81", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": null, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": null, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "NTAS1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76b2c52ffa3c944600df"], "subjects": ["615d708dbd4a37c4058ee5a8"], "chapters": ["615d6fed2b295b085ab6eb9e"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [{"title": "NTA Abhyas Paper", "value": "59", "isVisible": true}], "previousYearPapers": [], "question": {"text": "Two point masses,&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>m</mi></math> each carrying charges <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mi>q</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>+</mo><mi>q</mi></math> are attached to the ends of a massless rigid non-conducting wire of length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math>. When this arrangement is placed in a uniform electric field, then it deflects through an angle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>\u03b8</mi></math>. The minimum time needed by the rod to align itself along the field is", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "u7RMl", "text": "<math><mn>2</mn><mi>\u03c0</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>q</mi><mi>E</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "kdKMe", "text": "<math><mfrac><mrow><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi><mi>E</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "rxPTR", "text": "<math><mi>\u03c0</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>q</mi><mi>E</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "xKuZA", "text": "<math><mn>2</mn><mi>\u03c0</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mn>3</mn><mi>m</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>q</mi><mi>E</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "When the wire is brought in a uniform field E, then the torque is given by<br /><br /><math><mi>\u03c4</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>q</mi><mi>E</mi><mi>L</mi><mrow><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">sin</mi></mrow><mo>\u2061</mo><mrow><mi>\u03b8</mi></mrow></mrow></math><br /><br /><math><mo>=</mo><mi>q</mi><mi>E</mi><mi>L</mi><mi>\u03b8</mi></math> <math><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mo>\u2235</mo><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>\u03b8</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>i</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>v</mi><mi>e</mi><mi>r</mi><mi>y</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>s</mi><mi>m</mi><mi>a</mi><mi>l</mi><mi>l</mi></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><br />The moment of inertia of rod AB about O is<br /><br /><math><mi>I</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>m</mi><msup><mrow><mfenced separators=\"|\"><mrow><mfrac><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><msup><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br />As <math><mi>\u03c4</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>I</mi><mi>\u03b1</mi></math><br /><br /><img src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/nta_abhyas/jee_main/images/zqhpsfkovcktorvqclzxskayiafgtloiswbqqzrzgpgrxltnwg.jpeg\" /><br /><br />So, <math><mi>\u03b1</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>\u03c4</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>I</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>2q</mi><mi>E</mi><mi>L</mi><mi>\u03b8</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><msup><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br /><math><mo>\u21d2</mo><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><msup><mrow><mi>\u03c9</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi>\u03b8</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi><mi>E</mi><mi>L</mi><mi>\u03b8</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><msup><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow></mfrac></math> <math><mfenced close=\"]\" open=\"[\" separators=\"|\"><mrow><mo>\u2235</mo><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>\u03b1</mi><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mi>\u03c9</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mi>\u03b8</mi></mrow></mfenced></math><br /><br /><math><mo>\u21d2</mo><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><mi>&nbsp;</mi><msup><mrow><mi>\u03c9</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi><mi>E</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br />The time period of the wire is<br /><br /><math><mi>T</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>\u03c9</mi></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>\u03c0</mi><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><msup><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi><mi>E</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math><br /><br />The rod will become parallel to the field in time <math><mfrac><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><br /><br />So, <math><mi>t</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>T</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>4</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>\u03c0</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><msqrt><mfrac><mrow><mi>m</mi><mi>L</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>q</mi><mi>E</mi></mrow></mfrac></msqrt></math>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "cpyqbSubjects": ["61bb58181213731910ea0b70", "61c055eae8ce0dc8a5c62d33", "616057750283de43c87e3e1b", "61964fe0a5a5260118868021", "61964f81a5a526011886801d", "629f39e4ac11b26562e0625b", "616057920283de43c87e3e1e", "615f0c729476412f48314dab", "61a8a2c